{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.8",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 8,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 8 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:1",
      "text": "Doesn’t wisdom cry out? Doesn’t understanding raise her voice?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:2",
      "text": "On the top of high places by the way, where the paths meet, she stands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:3",
      "text": "Beside the gates, at the entry of the city, at the entry doors, she cries aloud:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:4",
      "text": "“I call to you men! I send my voice to the sons of mankind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:5",
      "text": "You simple, understand prudence! You fools, be of an understanding heart!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:6",
      "text": "Hear, for I will speak excellent things. The opening of my lips is for right things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:7",
      "text": "For my mouth speaks truth. Wickedness is an abomination to my lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:8",
      "text": "All the words of my mouth are in righteousness. There is nothing crooked or perverse in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:9",
      "text": "They are all plain to him who understands, right to those who find knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:10",
      "text": "Receive my instruction rather than silver, knowledge rather than choice gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:11",
      "text": "For wisdom is better than rubies. All the things that may be desired can’t be compared to it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:12",
      "text": "“I, wisdom, have made prudence my dwelling. Find out knowledge and discretion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:13",
      "text": "The fear of Yahweh is to hate evil. I hate pride, arrogance, the evil way, and the perverse mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:14",
      "text": "Counsel and sound knowledge are mine. I have understanding and power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:15",
      "text": "By me kings reign, and princes decree justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:16",
      "text": "By me princes rule, nobles, and all the righteous rulers of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:17",
      "text": "I love those who love me. Those who seek me diligently will find me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:18",
      "text": "With me are riches, honor, enduring wealth, and prosperity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:19",
      "text": "My fruit is better than gold, yes, than fine gold, my yield than choice silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:20",
      "text": "I walk in the way of righteousness, in the middle of the paths of justice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:21",
      "text": "that I may give wealth to those who love me. I fill their treasuries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:22",
      "text": "“Yahweh possessed me in the beginning of his work, before his deeds of old.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:23",
      "text": "I was set up from everlasting, from the beginning, before the earth existed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:24",
      "text": "When there were no depths, I was born, when there were no springs abounding with water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:25",
      "text": "Before the mountains were settled in place, before the hills, I was born;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:26",
      "text": "while as yet he had not made the earth, nor the fields, nor the beginning of the dust of the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:27",
      "text": "When he established the heavens, I was there. When he set a circle on the surface of the deep,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:28",
      "text": "when he established the clouds above, when the springs of the deep became strong,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:29",
      "text": "when he gave to the sea its boundary, that the waters should not violate his commandment, when he marked out the foundations of the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:30",
      "text": "then I was the craftsman by his side. I was a delight day by day, always rejoicing before him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:31",
      "text": "rejoicing in his whole world. My delight was with the sons of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:32",
      "text": "“Now therefore, my sons, listen to me, for blessed are those who keep my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:33",
      "text": "Hear instruction, and be wise. Don’t refuse it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:34",
      "text": "Blessed is the man who hears me, watching daily at my gates, waiting at my door posts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:35",
      "text": "For whoever finds me finds life, and will obtain favor from Yahweh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.8.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:36",
      "text": "But he who sins against me wrongs his own soul. All those who hate me love death.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
